SIMPLE: insolvable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insolvable
<hw>In*solv"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
solvable; insoluble; admitting no solution or explanation; <as>as, an
<ex>insolvable</ex> problem or difficulty</as>.</def> <rj><au>I.
Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Incapable of being paid or discharged, as
debts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not capable of being loosed or disentangled;
inextricable.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Bands <xex>insolvable</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insolvency</ent>⟦br⟧
